It&#8217;s understood the suspect allegedly broke into the victim's home, where she was sleeping alone and stabbed her multiple times. JOHANNESBURG - Police in Limpopo say the man arrested for the murder of a 17-year-old grade 11 pupil will appear before the Giyani Magistrates Court tomorrow.It s understood the suspect allegedly broke into the victim's home, where she was sleeping alone and stabbed her multiple times.The motive for the murder is still under investigation, but the victim, moments before dying, apparently told relatives the suspect was responsible for the stabbing The police's Moatshe Ngoepe says: The family members responded after hearing her screaming. She told them who attacked her. While they tried to call the ambulance, she was gone. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)